        "uuid": "75bc65a9_1ecccd6b",
        "filename": "lucicfg/starlark/stdlib/internal/luci/rules/builder.star",
        "patchSetId": 3
      },
      "lineNbr": 69,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-09T01:54:01Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hm. They can use \u0027triggers\u0027/\u0027triggered_by\u0027 (e.g. to prepare the CQ to expect this), but buildbucket ACLs will have to be modified manually (by adding acl.entry(...) to core.bucket(..., acls\u003d...)).\n\nThe problem is that buildbucket ACLs are very coarse. I don\u0027t want to allow a builder to trigger _any_ other builder by default whenever \u0027triggers\u003d...\u0027 is used, since I believe in majority of cases (at least in Chromium) this is harmful and not necessary, since triggering is done through Scheduler and Scheduler\u0027s ACLs are per-job, so we can surgically change only what we want there.\n\nAdded the explanation to the doc. I consider this a niche use case though, so I think we can tolerate this edge case.",
      "parentUuid": "eee8a35c_82c01dc4",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 67,
        "startChar": 2,
        "endLine": 69,
        "endChar": 0
      },
