      },
      "lineNbr": 94,
      "author": {
        "id": 1002539
      },
      "writtenOn": "2019-01-09T02:32:49Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "When we have builder tags, will we ever use swarming_tags separately from builder_tags?\n\nI named this just \"tags\" because most other scheduling-related attributes here (dimensions, priority, etc) do not have \u0027swarming_\u0027 prefix in them, even though they are passed directly to Swarming and Buildbucket doesn\u0027t really care about them.\n\n\u003e Alternatively, we can leave this as is, but repurpose later when builder gains builder-level tags.\n\nWhen we introduce builder tags, will we be able to say that \"all builder tags are passed to Swarming as swarming tags unaltered\"?",
      "parentUuid": "b51098e4_bc506281",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 94,
        "startChar": 4,
        "endLine": 94,
        "endChar": 8
      },
      "revId": "680774131aaffada67a9ce6be0e989966789089a",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
